body.description: 2 Packs S23 Ultra Tempered Glass Screen Protectors with two Camera Lens Protectors -- Only for S23Ultra 6.8 Inch, Not for any other Models.ATTENTION: Activate the Touch Sensitivity Setting as follows,1: Open "Settings"2: Navigate to "Advanced Features"3: On the bottom, find and activate "Touch Sensitivity"and After pasting the tempered film, re-scan your fingerprint of the same finger twice at different angles to unlock more sensitively (IMPORTANTLY)*NOTE* QUICK & EASY INSTALLATION-No bubbles1 - Clean and dry your screen with included wet cloth and dry cloth.2 - Use "Dust absorber" to absorb any dust on screen.3 - Carefully peel off the backing of the screen protector.3 - Line up and apply the film to the screen.5 - Tightly press the edges about 35s of the film to avoid edge lifting. 6- Press outwards the fingerprint circle to ensure no bubbles or adhesives. (IMPORTANTLY). Product Feature: —Support Ultrasonic Screen Fingerprint, Compatible with Face Recognition. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 17, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars TOO SMALL FOR LARGE SIZE ADULT SHOES!!
reviews.reviewText: I was very disappointed with this organizer. My flip-flops were the only shoes that would fit in it. Granted I do have large feet, size 10 or 11 but the description said that it could hold men and women shoes. So I assumed my shoes would fit in it.. I couldn't even fit the toe box of the shoe in the slot. I gave it three stars because it does seem to be good quality and small shoes will fit in it. If you have small feet or want it for your children then I think you'll be happy with it. Otherwise find something else.UPDATE: The seller contacted me and was kind enough to give me a full refund, unsolicited. Needless to say I was very impressed. I will be happy to do business with them in the future knowing that if I have a problem I can contact them and expect a fair outcome.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cards Work Great!
reviews.reviewText: Tried to use a hotel proximity card on my room's reader with RFID card and the reader light showed a signal (indicator lighted up white), but the door would not open. The RFID card was in my wallet's card section with the room card in the dollar bill section (closest to the reader), wallet placed against the reader. Removed the proximity card from my wallet, placed the card near the reader, reader indicator turned green and the door unlocked without issue. Worked great!
